[K]arim [I]nference [T]ool - KIT

o PREREQUISITES
	- Java Runtime Environment	>= 1.5	www.java.com/fr/download/
	- Weka 						>= 3	sourceforge.net/projects/weka/
	- GraphViz					>= 2	www.graphviz.org/Download.php
	 
o INSTALLATION
	- Add dot executable to the PATH
	- Weka.jar has to be in the CLASSPATH

o USAGE
	- KIT
		Usage : KIT systemName [Options]
		
		Options
			> General
			    --help | -h       : Show help
			> Algorithm
				--tree			  : Use tree inference (only for mealy)
		        -I                : Initial input symbols (a,b,c)");
                -Z                : Initial distinguishing sequences (a-b,a-c,a-c-b)");
                				
			    --reuseop         : Reuse output parameter for non closed row
			    --forcej48        : Force the use of J48 algorithm instead of M5P for numeric classes
			    --supportmin (20) : Minimal support for relation (1-100)
			> Output
			    --outdir (.)      : Where to save arff and graph files
			    --text            : Use the text logger
			    --html            : Use HTML logger
			    --openhtml        : Open HTML log automatically

		Ex: KIT drivers.efsm.NSPKDriver --outdir mydir --text
	
	
o BUGS
	Send an email to hossen@imag.fr with the complete logs and details
	
o TIPS
	- How to use more than 2Go of ram ?
		You need to have 64-bit (x64) processor and Java Runtime.
		Then add this option to the VM : -d64 -Xmx?g
		Replacing ? by the size of ram you want tu use in gigabytes
